Subject: [RECONSTRUCTION] Point Debian rules at user-local GNU make

The VM has no /usr/bin/make. This research-only shebang change lets the
packaging script reach its next dependency check using the extracted official
Ubuntu GNU Make binary. It is not part of the published IVXV tree.

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -1,3 +1,3 @@
-#!/usr/bin/make -f
+#!/home/audit/tools/usr/bin/make -f

 # See debhelper(7) (uncomment to enable)
